### Overview
This Python script is designed to create and manage text files containing information about football teams and their players. 
The script reads and writes data related to players' names and positions for each team. 
The teams included in this example are Galatasaray, Fenerbahçe, Beşiktaş, and Trabzonspor.

### How to Use

#### 1. Running the Script
Make sure you have Python installed on your system.
Copy and paste the provided code into a Python script file (e.g., football_teams_script.py).
Run the script.

### 2. Output Files
The script will create a text file for each football team (e.g., Galatasaray.txt, Fenerbahçe.txt, etc.) in the current working directory.

### 3. File Content
Each team's text file contains lines of player information in the format player_name, position.
The first line in each file provides the headers futbolcular,mevki.

### 4. Viewing Player Information
After running the script, you can check the generated text files to view the player information for each team.

## File Structure
football_teams_script.py: The main Python script file.
Galatasaray.txt, Fenerbahçe.txt, Beşiktaş.txt, Trabzonspor.txt: Text files containing player information for each team.
